This paper proposes a novel architecture for semantic segmentation using a squeeze-and-attention module. The paper focuses on computer vision tasks, specifically semantic segmentation, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper introduces a new attention mechanism, which is a popular topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed architecture also involves merging outputs from multiple stages, which is a common technique in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on public datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
